<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Citing <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_(typography)">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Point_(typography)</a>:</p>

<p>{quote}
the desktop publishing point (also called the PostScript point), which has been rounded to an even 72 points to the inch (1 point = 127⁄360 mm = 352.7 µm).
{quote}</p>

<p>However, point is declared as '0.00035' in Zend_Measure_Length.
According to the definition it should be 0.000352777778 meter.</p>

    </div>
</div>

